edu.xtec.jclic.bags

Class ActivitySequenceElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.xtec.jclic.bags.ActivitySequenceElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Editable, Domable, Cloneable

    public class ActivitySequenceElement
extends Object
implements Editable, Domable, Cloneable
    This class defines a specific point into a JClic sequence of activities: what activity must run at this point, what to do or where to jump when the activity finishes, the behavior of the "next" and "prev" buttons, etc. It can also have a "tag", used to refer to this point of the sequence with a unique name. ActivitySequenceElements are always stored into ActivitySequence objects.
    Version:
    13.09.10
    Author:
    Francesc Busquets (fbusquets@xtec.cat)
